Task
Does the array have at least one negative element?
Write the isNegativeInArray function that takes the arr array as an argument and returns true if the array contains at least one negative element, and false otherwise.
Example:
• the isNegativeInArray ([20, -26, -12]) function must return true;
• the isNegativeInArray ([2, 9, -10]) function must return true;
• the isNegativeInArray ([1, 2, 3, 4]) function must return false;
• the isNegativeInArray ([1, 0]) function must return false;
• the isNegativeInArray ([]) function must return false.

Solution
function isNegativeInArray (arr) {
  let negative = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i <arr.length; i ++) {
    if (arr [i] <0) {
    negative ++;
    break;
    }
    }
    if (negative === 1) return true;
    else return false;
}
